episodes.title: Epstein Survivors Will Attend Trump's State of the Union Address | Epstein Survivor Jess Michaels
episodes.description:
Susan Demas speaks with Epstein survivor Jess Michaels about what really happened at the Pam Bondi hearing—and why survivors say the cover-up is still ongoing.

From redacted names of powerful men to pressure inside Congress to “move on,” Jess details what she saw on Capitol Hill and why survivors are refusing to stay silent. She also reveals how the administration is handling the Epstein files—and what could happen next.

Plus: Jess shares the launch of her trauma-informed safety app, With You Too.

This is about justice. And it’s not over.

50:00 – Silence vs accountability

episodes.title: They Were Told to Stay Silent About Epstein
episodes.description:
Epstein survivor Jess Michaels reveals that Republican members of the Judiciary Committee were pressured not to speak about the Epstein files.

“They were going to be Massied.”

Inside Congress, members were allegedly warned to move on—or face consequences. This is the moment the silence became obvious.
